<p>$\solution$ <br />
In this case, the composed function is one of the given,<br />
\(\begin{align*}
	f(g(x)) &amp;= x
\end{align*}\)</p>

<p>Start with $f(x)$</p>

\[\begin{align*}
	f(x) &amp;= \frac{2}{x+1} \\
	f(g(x)) &amp;= \frac{2}{ g(x) +1}
\end{align*}\]

<p>Since $f(g(x))=x$,</p>

\[\begin{align*}
	\frac{2}{ g(x) +1} &amp;= x \\
	g(x) +1 &amp;= \frac{2}{x} \\
	g(x) &amp;= \frac{2}{x} -1		\tag*{(ans.)}
\end{align*}\]

<p>You can check your answer by composing the function,</p>

\[\begin{align*}
	f(x) &amp;= \frac{2}{x+1} \\
	f(g(x)) &amp;= 	\frac{2}{\br{ \frac{2}{x} -1 }+1} \\
	&amp;= \frac{2}{\frac{2}{x}} \\
	&amp;= x
\end{align*}\]

